metadata.name: E=B; #110
metadata.description:
- Last day with the dying planet -

A sentimental start.

It is the last day of this planet, you once lived and shared so many meaningful memories.

Take a last good look at the places of the planet. Look to the far side. You see people were leaving already. But you loved the planet so much that you dare to risk and stay a bit longer before you leave.

This moment becomes bottomless. Landscapes glitter vividly with altered gradients, fog emits at the far end of the land, and Energy leaks and escapes from the core, thru the cracks in form of aurora structure.

It is a mix of sadness, grief, missing, and anxiety.
It is the end.
It is breathtaking.
It makes you hesitate.

// About the scene
The planet was vast.
You may experience Rocky Sierra, Fluidy Mountains, Wide Dunes, and even Calm Ocean.

The Breakdown
In the rare case, you might be able to see a highly pixelated/extreme wide/flat landscape with finely emitted aurora, which is considered a rare scene. i.e. absolute strength of light vs breakdown of limited matters.

// About the presentation style
The Texture & The Drawing : Heavily inspired by pencil sketching techniques that emphasize shading and outline relationship towards an angular light source.

Apply color scheme from other Astro objects to give an alternative look for the planet.

The Animation Sequence: Custom storytelling algorithms combine the formation of the aurora, landscape, and scene detail all in a timeline. The resulting sequential narrative style illustrates the history of the landscape and the aurora formation.

Not just giving the collector the final look but also sharing the cause and reason of such composition.

The Tiny Zoom: A tiny zoom-out movement is implemented in the piece to echo the theme of the piece. i.e. leaving and departing the planet.

// About the Music
Two theme songs were made for this piece.

Theme I: [Solitude]
Theme II: [Fragmented]

Both songs were made to present the process of departure: the sleep of the planet and the awakening of the observer.

// Metaphor
We face departure and arrival all the time. They might be the best or the worst memories of our life. Whether you are willing to or not.

The ending is an ongoing process and on the other side of the Ending comes the beginning.

It is ok to be sentimental.

// Control
Best viewed in large and wide proportion.
(Open in new window)

[S] - save the scene once the drawing stops
[L] - leave and take a look at other places
[Mouse Click] - click twice to initiate music. then click one to mute/show


- 與垂死星球的最後一天 -

從感傷開始。

這是你曾經生活在的星球之最後一天，你們的關係將要結束，許多有意義的回憶也將封印成回憶。

看看遠方。其他人已經開始離開了。
你還留著，想好好看看這個星球。

你請願冒險，也要在離開之前多停留一段時間。

此刻像是無限。景觀隨著漸變的顏色而變得更加生動，在陸地的遠端散發出最後的火霧，能量從核心洩漏，以極光狀的結構從裂縫中逸出。

它是悲傷、內疚、思念和焦慮的混合體。
這是結束。
但又嘆為觀止。
讓你猶豫不決。

// 關於現場
這個星球曾經很大
您會經歷到寂靜的岳峰、流動的山脈、寬闊的沙丘以及平靜的海洋。

罕見的一刻 - 物質崩壞
在極少數情況下，您可能會看到極寬/平坦/鋸齒化的景觀與高像素細膩的極光並存，即光的絕對強度與有限的物質瓦解。

// 關於演示風格
紋理與繪畫風格 : 深受鉛筆素描技術的啟發，這些技術強調與角光源的陰影和輪廓關係。

應用其他天文物體的配色方案，為地球提供另一種外觀。

動畫序列 : 自定義敘事算法將極光、風景和場景細節的形成全部結合在一個時間軸中。由此產生的順序敘述風格，說明了景觀的歷史和極光的形成。

不僅給收藏家最終的外觀，而且還分享了這種構圖的原因和原因。

小變焦 : 作品中實施了微小的縮小運鏡，以呼應作品的主題 - 離開。

// 關於音樂
為作品製作了兩首主題曲。

主題一：【獨】
主題二：【碎】

兩首歌表達/呈現離開的過程：星球的沉睡和觀察者的覺醒。

// 隱喻
不管你願不願意，我們無時無刻都面臨著離去和到來。離去前它們是我們一生中最美好/最糟糕的回憶。

結局是一維，離開是二維的，另一端叫作開始。

覺得感傷是ok 的。

// 控制
但在大寬視窗下視覺效果最好
(Open in new window)

[S] - 繪圖停止後存取畫作
[L] - 離開去其他地方看看
[鼠標單擊] - 單擊兩次以啟動音樂。 然後單擊一個靜音/顯示

metadata.name: Abstract Life #31
metadata.description:
The concept of organic, obtained from living systems, is said to be an effect that, like a plant and a living being, has grown in a completely dynamic manner in different degrees, and no factor except vital forces has prevented its growth. Organic creation is an example of this type. Léonard de Vinci believed in nature; he wrote, "Painting is a child of nature" in his opinion, art should be compatible with nature. His public image of creativity was "innovation while maintaining fidelity" to nature. According to Michelangelo, the form the artist gives to the materials is in the artist's mind and the materials themselves. Therefore, the artist is always in a metaphysical struggle with the form and secrets of nature. This is a revelatory process through which the artist discovers the mass of paper already hidden in his mind and the materials. As an architect, I tried to create this work while paying attention to the structuralism of shapes and forms in creation, inspired by the colors in nature and my experience in painting and illustration.

To spread the vibe of my beautiful community, minters will own 50% of royalty on each secondary sale.
Eighteen different color palettes and three different borders are used in this artwork.
Made in p5js
Created August 2022
Artist: @ChistaAi

metadata.name: To my lips, your kisses and cigarettes #21
metadata.description:
A timid smoke rises from the ashtray, just a trace of what had been hours before, powerful smoke drifting through the room. A memory of the lighted flames illuminating the faces that were there, coming from many mouths, amid laughter, sips, drags, and lipsticks. 
Red, purple, orange, pink, beige... an ashtray of many palettes, an ashtray of many mouths. 
The smoke goes out and, like the fog that dissipates in the early hours of the day clearing the horizon, I realize: Sophie, Chloe, Lena, Zoe and Kylie... which of these mouths also took my heart?

15 layers
47 images
More than a trillion possibilities 

Laura Faria | @laufaria
2022
Digital Collage

metadata.name: CITYBLOCKS: GENESIS #97
metadata.description:
On desktop, open project in live view and click “S” to download STL file (printable / experimental)
Rotate and zoom with the mouse to explore the model

Cityblocks: Genesis

In the Cityblocks series, urban ensembles are generated with a simple click. With each iteration appears a new densely built city block. Graced with impeccable geometrical lines, devoid of any human presence, these buildings remind us of brutalist utopias like Le Corbusier’s Cité radieuse or Niemeyer’s Brasilia. But despite their clearly modernist feel, there is something hauntingly primitive about them. They could be either New Mexican adobe pueblos, Minoan palaces, or Turkish troglodyte dwellings. Both carved and sculpted, these Ghormenghasts of concrete float in a realm out of time, like in some architect’s dream.

The purpose of this creative work is to generate 3D architectural projects that could be implemented in the real world. The accelerating lives that we live, complicated by growing and unpredictable environmental crises, call for an enhanced capacity to come up quickly with new architectural solutions adapted to different contexts. From computer assisted design to 3D printing, from augmented reality to real-life housing, from sculpture to architecture, this work aims at bridging the gap between the virtual and the tangible.

Working as a visual artist, David Umemoto draws inspiration from his training as an architect. He has been using low-tech methods for a long time, refining his talent for elegant simple shapes and combinatory constructions. Now, poured concrete and home-made moulds are giving way to zero-gravity rotating models. The skills he developed while working with real objects find a new playground in the virtual realm.

metadata.name: Happy #106
metadata.description:
Impressions of happiness, generated with code.  Press [P] to animate/pause.

Paint strokes are generated in 3D using three.js. You can drag the mouse to explore different views of the same painting. Interactions require a GPU.
Keyboard controls:
[S] Save the current view.
[P] Play / Pause animation.
[F] Fill the screen.
[1] Save 9:16 image, 3375 x 6000px.
[2] Save 3:4 image, 3000 x 4000px.
[3] Save 1:1 square image, 4000 x 4000px. 
[4] Save 16:9 image, 6000 x 3375px.

Elsif, 2022.04
